---
title: What Did You Do This Week?
description: Talk about your week using past tense and days of the week
level: beginner
time: 20 minutes
---

# Grammar: Past Tense with Days

## Using Days of the Week

Use "el" before days when talking about a specific day. No "el" when talking about days in general.

El lunes fui al gimnasio.
  On Monday I went to the gym.

Los martes trabajo hasta tarde.
  On Tuesdays I work late. (in general)

## Common Irregular Past Tense

Some verbs you'll use a lot have irregular past tense forms.

Fui al cine.
  I went to the movies. (ir → fui)

Tuve mucho trabajo.
  I had a lot of work. (tener → tuve)

Hice ejercicio.
  I exercised. (hacer → hice)

Estuve ocupado/a.
  I was busy. (estar → estuve)

## Summarizing Your Week

When someone asks about your week, start with a general impression before giving details.

Tuve una semana ocupada.
  I had a busy week.

Fue una semana tranquila.
  It was a quiet week.

# Conjugation: ir (to go)
tense: Preterite (Past)
type: irregular
yo → fui [fwee]
tú → fuiste [FWEES-teh]
él/ella/usted → fue [fweh]
nosotros → fuimos [FWEE-mohs]
ellos/ellas/ustedes → fueron [FWEH-rohn]

