# Vocabulary: Street Week Talk (Northern Mexico)

Anduve bien ocupado/a.
  I was super busy.
  [ahn-DOO-beh bee-EHN oh-koo-PAH-doh]

No paré en toda la semana.
  I didn't stop all week.
  [noh pah-REH ehn TOH-dah lah seh-MAH-nah]

Estuvo pesada la semana.
  The week was rough.
  [ehs-TOO-boh peh-SAH-dah lah seh-MAH-nah]

Me la pasé en el jale.
  I spent the whole time at work.
  [meh lah pah-SEH ehn ehl HAH-leh]

Eché la floja.
  I lazed around.
  [EH-cheh lah FLOH-hah]

Salí a pistear.
  I went out drinking.
  [sah-LEE ah pees-teh-AHR]

No hice nada, la neta.
  I didn't do anything, honestly.
  [noh EE-seh NAH-dah lah NEH-tah]

Estuvo tranqui.
  It was chill.
  [ehs-TOO-boh TRAHN-kee]

# Phrases: Talking About Your Week

¿Qué hiciste esta semana?
  What did you do this week?
  [keh ee-SEES-teh EHS-tah seh-MAH-nah]

Esta semana...
  This week...
  [EHS-tah seh-MAH-nah]

El lunes...
  On Monday...
  [ehl LOO-nehs]

Tuve una semana ocupada.
  I had a busy week.
  [TOO-beh OO-nah seh-MAH-nah oh-koo-PAH-dah]

No hice mucho.
  I didn't do much.
  [noh EE-seh MOO-choh]

Fue una semana tranquila.
  It was a quiet week.
  [fweh OO-nah seh-MAH-nah trahn-KEE-lah]

